e\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36269,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/21\/islam-plus-hasanat\/","url_meta":{"origin":39858,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Tawbah: Embracing Islam plus good deeds","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 21, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Tawil reported: He came to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \u201cWhat do you think of a man who commits every sin, leaving nothing of them. Is there repentance for him?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cHave you embraced Islam?\u201d He said, \u201cAs for\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36480,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/06\/01\/deeds-not-accepted\/","url_meta":{"origin":39858,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Rahim: Deeds not accepted from estranged relatives","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 1, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, the deeds of the children of Adam are presented every Thursday, when night turns into Friday. The deeds are not accepted from one who severed his family ties.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 10272 Grade: Hasan (fair)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19081,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/05\/10\/deeds-not-accepted-murderer\/","url_meta":{"origin":39858,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Murder: Good deeds not accepted from killers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 10, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"'Ubadah ibn al-Samit reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever kills a believer without a just cause, Allah will not accept any of his obligatory or voluntary good deeds.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4270 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u0628\u064e\u0627\u062f\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0645\u0650\u062a\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17409,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/01\/quickest-deeds-rewarded-punished\/","url_meta":{"origin":39858,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Deeds: Fastest deeds to be rewarded or punished","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 1, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe quickest good deeds to be rewarded are righteousness and upholding family ties. The quickest evil deeds to be punished are transgression and severing family ties.\u201d Source: Sunan Ibn Ma\u0304jah 4212 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Suyuti\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\